.TH MPF-CHECK 1 "June 2026" "MPF" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mpf-check \- generate Redump !submissionInfo.txt from finished optical-media dumps
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mpf-check
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.IR DUMP-DIRECTORY
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mpf-check
(upstream \fBMPF.Check\fR) reads the log files left next to a finished
optical-media dump and writes a \fI!submissionInfo.txt\fR alongside in
the Redump submission format. It is the validator/finalize step of the
Media Preservation Frontend (MPF) suite.

Supported dump sources include
.BR redumper (1),
.BR aaru (1),
.BR discimagecreator (1),
Cleanrip and UmdImageCreator. The tool autodetects which dumper was
used by looking at the surrounding log filenames and structure.

When run with no arguments
.B mpf-check
prints its full help text.

A secondary mode performs live copy-protection scans on a drive via
\fB--path\fR / \fB--scan\fR; this path uses vendor SCSI commands and
therefore requires
.B CAP_SYS_RAWIO
(already set on the shipped binary, so no sudo).
.SH DRIVE ACCESS
File capabilities replace
.B sudo
for SCSI passthrough. Read access on
.I /dev/sr*
is granted automatically via
.B uaccess
when logged in at a local desktop seat; for headless or SSH use add the
user to the
.B cdrom
group:
.PP
.RS
.B sudo usermod -aG cdrom $USER
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Generate submission info next to a finished redumper dump:
.RS
.B mpf-check ~/dumps/disc01/
.RE
.PP
Scan a drive for copy protection:
.RS
.B mpf-check --path /dev/sr0 --scan
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib64/mpf-check/MPF.Check
The actual self-contained .NET binary (cap_sys_rawio=ep).
.TP
.I /usr/bin/mpf-check
Shell wrapper that exec\(aqs the binary above.
